
[1]disappointment

   DISAPPOINTMENT, n. Defeat or failure of expectation, hope, wish, desire
   or intention; miscarriage of design or plan.

   We are apt to complain of the disappointment of our hopes and schemes,
   but disappointments often prove blessings and save us from calamity or
   ruin.
